    <h1>For your convenience, our Chinese recipes are divided into an assortment of different categories, listed to your left.</h1>
	<p>Before you browse through the categories, there are a few  tidbits that we'd like to point out which are essential to creating great Chinese dishes. </p>
     <ul id="ulTopBox">
	<li>Alway use young, fresh, and tender vegetables when possible</li>
    <li>Avoid using frozen ingredients because it will not taste nearly as good as using fresh ones </li>
    <li>The marinade, and seasoning sauce should be prepared ahead of time </li>
    <li>The ingredients must be washed and should be sorted and cut prior to cooking. </li>
    </ul>
	<p>These are particularly important in Chinese cooking, as the essence of Chinese cuisine is to achieve food tenderness through quick cooking to retain the natural taste, flavor, and color of the ingredients. </p>
	<h2>Many of our Chinese cooking recipes may seem lengthy.  But don't be intimidated by that, as we painstakingly go through each recipe that we put in our database to explain each step as detailed and easy to follow as possible. As you will find out soon, that majority of time spend in cooking Chinese dishes is in the preparation, and the actual cooking time is much shorter. If you have any questions about these recipes, need clarifications, comments, etc., please feel free to contact us.  Happy Chinese cooking!</h2>
	<p>We are constantly adding more recipes to our database, so please bookmark us and keep checking in for new recipes, or join our weekly newsletter for updates. </p>
	<p>Want to share your recipes? Send your recipe to us <a href="../contactus/contactus.htm">Here</a>. Once approved, we will publish your recipe with your name and a link to you (if available). </p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
